{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Adds a message filter. Filters are handlers that are run on all","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"incoming and outgoing messages, prior to standard dispatch. Filters"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are run in the order that they were added.  The same handler can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"added as a filter more than once, in which case it will be run more","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"than once.  Filters added during a filter callback won’t be run on","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the message being processed. Filter functions are allowed to modify"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and even drop messages."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnectionprotocol\/addfilter(filterfunction:userdata:userdatafreefunc:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionProtocol"]]},"metadata":{"title":"addFilter(filterFunction:userData:userDataFreeFunc:)","extendedModule":"GIO","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO22DBusConnectionProtocolPAAE9addFilter14filterFunction8userData0iJ8FreeFuncSiSpySo13_GDBusMessageVGSgSpySo01_mC0VGSg_AKs5Int32VSvSgtXC_ARyARXCSgtF","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addFilter","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"filterFunction","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GDBusMessageFilterFunction","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDBusMessageFilterFunction"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"userDataFreeFunc","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GDestroyNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@GDestroyNotify"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionProtocol\/addFilter(filterFunction:userData:userDataFreeFunc:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addFilter"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"filterFunction"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GDBusMessageFilterFunction","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDBusMessageFilterFunction","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"userDataFreeFunc","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@GDestroyNotify","text":"GDestroyNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that filters are run in a dedicated message handling thread so","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"they can’t block and, generally, can’t do anything but signal a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"worker thread. Also note that filters are rarely needed - use API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"such as ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_dbus_connection_send_message_with_reply()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_subscribe()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"g_dbus_connection_call()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a filter consumes an incoming message the message is not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dispatched anywhere else - not even the standard dispatch machinery","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(that API such as "},{"code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_subscribe()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_send_message_with_reply()"},{"type":"text","text":" relies on) will see the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"message. Similarly, if a filter consumes an outgoing message, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"message will not be sent to the other peer.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"userDataFreeFunc","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is non-"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", it will be called (in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"thread-default main context of the thread you are calling this","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"method from) at some point after ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"userData"},{"text":" is no longer","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"needed. (It is not guaranteed to be called synchronously when the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"filter is removed, and may be called after ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"connection"},{"type":"text","text":" has been"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"destroyed.)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusConnectionProtocol/addFi